@startuml fig-A01-message-flow
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title SDN Firewall — E2 PCAP Flow (Policy → Traffic → Evidence)

participant "Policy File\n(YAML)" as PF #FFF9C4
participant "Controller\n(Python)" as C #E1BEE7
participant "s1\n(OVS)" as S #BBDEFB
participant "h1\n(client)" as H1 #FFE0B2
participant "h2\n(server)" as H2 #C8E6C9
participant "tcpdump" as CAP #ECEFF1

== PHASE 1 — RULE INSTALLATION ==

PF -> C : load policy (allowed/blocked flows)
C -> S : flow-mod: allow h1→h2:80 (priority 100)
C -> S : flow-mod: drop h1→h2 ICMP (priority 200)
S --> C : barrier-reply (rules committed)

== PHASE 2 — ALLOWED TRAFFIC ==

H1 -[#43A047]> S : SYN h1→h2:80
S -[#43A047]> H2 : SYN (forwarded by allow rule)
H2 -[#43A047]-> S : SYN-ACK
S -[#43A047]-> H1 : SYN-ACK
H1 -[#43A047]> S : ACK + HTTP GET
note right of CAP : R3: >=5 IP data-plane packets

== PHASE 3 — BLOCKED TRAFFIC ==

H1 -[#E53935]> S : ICMP Echo Request
S -[#E53935]>x S : drop (matches drop rule)
note right of S #FFEBEE : no reply — blocked by flow entry

== EVIDENCE COLLECTION ==

S -> CAP : traffic_e2.pcap
C -> CAP : controller logs
S -> CAP : ovs-ofctl dump-flows

legend right
  R1: tcp.port==6653 >= 1 (OpenFlow present)
  R2: tcp.port==6653 && tcp.len>0 >= 5
  R3: ip && (tcp||udp||icmp) >= 5
  PCAP must show allowed and blocked flows.
endlegend
@enduml
